04811nam a22008535i 9783110428964DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20152016gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)1013956288  a97831104289647 a10.1515/97831104289642doi  a(DE-B1597)452379  a(OCoLC)940672638  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aBS1765b.H363 2016 7aREL0060902bisacsh04a229/.4049223  aBC 4340qSEPA2rvk0(DE-625)rvk/9433:1 aHambardzumyan, Garegin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Book of Sirach in the Armenian Biblical Tradition :bYakob Nalean and His Commentary on Sirach /cGaregin Hambardzumyan. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2015] 4c©2016  a1 online resource (228 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aDeuterocanonical and Cognate Literature Studies ,x1865-1666 ;v3300tFrontmatter -- tAcknowledgments -- tContents -- tAbbreviations -- t1. Introduction -- t2. The Armenian Version of Sirach -- t3. Yakob Nalean’s commentary on Sirach -- t4. The Main themes of Sirach discussed by Yacob Nalean -- t5. Conclusions -- tBibliography -- tIndex of names -- tSubject index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe extreme complexity of Sirach’s text at times makes it almost impossible to come to one clear conclusion as regards certain issues. There are numerous differences between various translations of this deuterocanonical text. In addition, the Armenian translation, being a textual witness to not one but multiple parent texts, has its own complications.This research provides a sustained theological reading of the Armenian text of Sirach on the basis of Yakob Nalean’s commentary written in the 18th century. At the same time it places a great emphasis on the textual evaluation of the various versions of Sirach in Armenian. In this respect an attempt has been made to display the unique features of the Armenian Sirach within the wider scope of the scholarship of this biblical text. Through a comprehensive linguistic and theological analysis of some major parts of Sirach in Armenian, this study assesses the extent to which this book was in use amongst Armenians throughout the centuries. In particular, the numerous references to Sirach in both Armenian and non-Armenian patristic literature are examined, with the aim of dating the first translations into Armenian and tracing the development of the text in the Armenian medieval schools.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aApokryphen. 4aArmenische Bibel. 4aSirach. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aApocrypha.  aArmenian Bible.  aSirach.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104290530 cprintz978311043163640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311042896440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110428964423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110428964/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2015  aZDB-23-DGGb2015